1
00:00:04,225 --> 00:00:08,950
My child, these may be the last words I get to leave you

2
00:00:10,275 --> 00:00:14,791
I've always thought of the characters in my stories as my children

3
00:00:15,793 --> 00:00:20,538
Loving each one of them just like a mother would

4
00:00:22,497 --> 00:00:27,309
But you are the most extraordinary of them all

5
00:00:28,025 --> 00:00:32,751
You alone can defy the fate of this world

6
00:00:33,497 --> 00:00:36,975
And write the perfect ending to my story

7
00:00:38,525 --> 00:00:42,832
You alone shall leave these pages...

8
00:00:44,604 --> 00:00:46,952
For a future I will not see

9
00:00:48,422 --> 00:00:52,871
Still, I say to you... Fly, my sweet child

10
00:00:53,627 --> 00:00:58,937
Just like a forest breeze yearns for the open sky

11
00:00:59,040 --> 00:01:04,531
Head into the unknown and seek an adventure to call your own

12
00:01:06,897 --> 00:01:12,619
If you meet a dragon bright as a thousand jewels, dance through the air together

13
00:01:16,758 --> 00:01:22,995
You are not alone, for this world has accepted your place in it

14
00:01:24,845 --> 00:01:29,860
Do not lose heart. You still have many wishes left to fulfill

15
00:01:34,682 --> 00:01:38,087
A long tale awaits you, my love

16
00:01:39,936 --> 00:01:45,441
Let songs and flowers be the ink that fills its pages

17
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:52,521
Take my pen and use it to continue your story

